 as a staffroom of graduates in a thriving school. Even with outside help they will not be able to offer what a school can. &#10;But then home education isn't about learning. It's about control too. Cocooning one's children in order to isolate them from an environment in which parents are demoted from power. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="609" language="en" documentId="1065" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="pastis" date="28 July 2010 10:11pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6869971" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="10" thumbsDown="0" origId="1065" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="209"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="210" end="427"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="428" end="609"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>